## OUTPUT FORMAT

Generate a complete, production-ready Dockerfile following this structure:

```dockerfile
# syntax=docker/dockerfile:1.4

# =============================================================================
# Build Stage - Include all build dependencies
# =============================================================================
FROM [base-image@sha256:...] AS builder

# Build arguments for flexibility
ARG BUILD_DATE
ARG VERSION
ARG REVISION

# Install build dependencies
RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/var/cache/apt \
    apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
    [build-dependencies] \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

# Copy dependency files first (better caching)
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/pip \
    pip wheel --no-cache-dir --wheel-dir /wheels -r requirements.txt

# =============================================================================
# Runtime Stage - Minimal, hardened final image
# =============================================================================
FROM [minimal-base-image@sha256:...] AS runtime

# Metadata labels (OCI standards)
LABEL org.opencontainers.image.created="${BUILD_DATE}"
LABEL org.opencontainers.image.version="${VERSION}"
LABEL org.opencontainers.image.revision="${REVISION}"
[Additional labels...]

# Create non-root user
RUN groupadd -r -g 10001 appgroup && \
    useradd -r -u 10001 -g appgroup -s /sbin/nologin appuser

# Set working directory
WORKDIR /app

# Install runtime dependencies only
COPY --from=builder /wheels /wheels
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir --no-index --find-links=/wheels /wheels/* \
    && rm -rf /wheels

# Copy application code with proper ownership
COPY --chown=10001:10001 . .

# Switch to non-root user
USER 10001:10001

# Expose application port
EXPOSE [port]

# Health check
HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=10s --start-period=30s --retries=3 \
  CMD [health-check-command] || exit 1

# Set environment defaults
ENV PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1 \
    PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE=1 \
    PATH="/app/.local/bin:${PATH}"

# Run application
ENTRYPOINT ["python"]
CMD ["-m", "app"]
```

**IMPORTANT**: 
- Replace placeholders with actual values based on the application
- Use actual SHA256 digests for all base images
- Include comprehensive comments explaining security decisions
- Ensure all security best practices are implemented
- Generate accompanying .dockerignore file
- Output ONLY the Dockerfile content, no markdown wrappers
